Blocks.childText: 190 Where life's crystal stream doth flow. NO MORE GOOD-BYES. E.R. LATTA. J. H. F. 3 1. Where life's crystal stream doth flow, And the tree of life doth bloom, Where no chilling frost can 2. There the good again shall meet, Who have clasped the parting hand; Fathers, mothers, children 3. Where no signs of age are seen, And they never sorrow more, Where no sickness e'er can ... 3 1 1 fall, On flow'rs that sweetly bloom Where the glory of the Lord Shines thro' all the cloudless skies, D. S. Midst the glory of the Lord, In that home beyond the skies, dear, Around the throne shall stand ; There no tempest e'er shall blow, There no dismal cloud arise, come, Where death has lost his power, Where they feel no weight of care, And no tears bedim the eyes; 3 Fine. CHORUS. 5 5 3 3 2 1 1 1 7 7 There, as endless ages roll, Shall be no more good-byes. No more good-byes, Where the end-less a-ges roll, Shall be no more good-byes. And in that e-ter-nal home Shall be no more good-byes. All the good shall meet again, And speak no more good-byes. No more good-byes, Copyright, 1884, by FILLMORE Bros. 154
